extends /shared/layout
block content
   +pageTitle()(teach="gsl")
   .lg-section
      .uk-container.uk-container-center
         .uk-grid
            .uk-width-medium-4-10
               h2 Living Factors
               .lg-index-items
                  .lg-index-box-text
                     p.
                        Great Salt Lake is teeming with life. The organisms that live in and around Great Salt Lake depend on one another and their environment for survival.
                  +index-item('Great Salt Lake Food Web','interactive explore','foodweb','images/foodweb.jpg')
                     p Learn about the producers and consumers that make up the Great Salt Lake food web.
                  +index-item('Brine Shrimp Life Cycle','interactive explore','artemia','images/artemia.jpg')
                     p.
                        Brine shrimp are the largest animals that live in Great Salt Lake. This unique organism has several adaptations that help it survive in its extreme environment.
                  +index-item('Microbes at Work','learn more','microbes','images/microbes.jpg')
                     p Microbes are everywhere, and they play many important roles in the natural world.
                  +index-item('Investigating Microbial Diversity: Then and Now','learn more','diversity','images/diversity.jpg')
                     p.
                        Microbes are some of the oldest and most diverse live forms on the planet. Read about how scientists study these tiny creatures.

            .uk-width-medium-6-10
               h2 Non-Living Factors
               .lg-index-items
                  .lg-index-box-text
                     p.
                        An ecosystem is largely shaped by its physical environment, including factors such as climate, geology, and mineral content. These non-living factors determine which organisms survive and thrive in an ecosystem.
                  +index-item('Meet the Microenvironments','interactive explore','micro','images/micro.jpg')
                     p.
                        Great Salt Lake is divided into a variety of regions, each with its own defining characteristics.
                  +index-item('Physical Characteristics of Great Salt Lake','learn more','physical_char','images/physical_char.jpg')
                     p The physical environment in and around Great Salt Lake is varied, dynamic, and often extreme.
                  +index-item('Water In, Water Out','interactive explore','water','images/water.jpg')
                     p Lake level and salinity are influenced by how much water flows in and out.
                  +index-item('Great Salt Lake From Space','explore','space','images/space.jpg')
                     p See two and a half years of changes compressed into 30 seconds.
                  +index-item('Monitoring and Studying Great Salt Lake','learn more','monitor','images/monitor.jpg')
                     p Scientists work to understand human-lake interactions and maximize the lake&apos;s resources.
                  +index-item('Great Salt Lake Throughout the Year','interactive explore','year','images/year.jpg')
                     p.
                        No matter when you visit Great Salt Lake, there&apos;s always something to see. This guide will tell you what to look for in any season.
